    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Air Compressor and Power Steering
        Pump - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Air Compressor</title>
            <figure id="f3350009245" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figK16/K16003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air compressor mounting and connections</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M18 elbow assembly (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hose (coolant) .50 ID (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor (oil supply) hose assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 50 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Drain hose (oil)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 80 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 elbow assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two M10 x 30 bolts connecting the air compressor bracket to the air compressor
                    and finger tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new air compressor gasket on the front cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, get assistance to remove and install the air compressor
                        and power steering pump assembly.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With help from an assistant, install air compressor assembly into front cover while
                    aligning air compressor gear with the lower idler gear. Install two M12 x 50 bolts through air
                    compressor bracket into crankcase and finger tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align air compressor bolt holes with the front cover bolt holes and install two M12 x 80
                    bolts finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not over torque air compressor mounting bolts. Over tightening
                        bolts will result in a fractured front cover.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten two M12 x 80 bolts connecting the air compressor to the front cover to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_223.xml" xrefid="t335000902">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335000902"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten two M10 x 30 bolts connecting the air compressor to the air compressor bracket
                    to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_223.xml" xrefid="t335000902">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335000902"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push up on rear of air compressor and tighten two M12 x 50 bolts connecting the air
                    compressor bracket to the crankcase to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_223.xml" xrefid="t335000902">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335000902"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all elbow assemblies and hose connector assemblies removed from the crankcase
                    and air compressor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Orient elbow assemblies to reduce hose stress. Tighten elbow assemblies and hose
                    connector assemblies to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_223.xml" xrefid="t335000902">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335000902"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install air compressor (oil supply) hose assembly on M10 elbow assembly. Finger tighten
                    hose nut and then turn nut 1/2 to 2 additional turns until tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install oil drain hose and tighten hose clamps.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
